  {
    "ts": "2026-03-24T06:10:34+00:00",
    "headline": "Estee Lauder in talks to merge with Jean Paul Gaultier-owner Puig",
    "summary": "<body><p>STORY: Estee Lauder and Spanish beauty group Puig said Monday they are discussing a merger.&nbsp;</p><p>The deal would create a $40 billion luxury beauty group, and put brands such as Tom Ford, Carolina Herrera and Clinique under one roof.</p><p>The deal comes as the global fragrance industry faces a slowdown after years of strong post-pandemic growth.</p><p>It could also help drive Estee Lauder's turnaround efforts after the company's annual outlook fell short of Wall Street estimates.</p><p>A source ​familiar with the deal told Reuters that another part of the rationale is that a combined company will better compete with French giant L'Oreal.</p><p>But one analyst said it could just \"saddle Estée Lauder with more problems.\"</p><p>Puig, home to iconic perfume lines from Jean Paul Gaultier and Byredo, last month reported slowing growth in fragrances.</p><p>Shares of Estee Lauder fell sharply on news of the plan, ending Monday's session more than 7% lower.</p></body>",
    "url": "https://finance.yahoo.com/video/estee-lauder-talks-merge-jean-061034206.html",
    "source": "Reuters Videos",
    "provider": "yfinance",
